  "help": [
    {
      "textLabel": "This tool helps you estimate your monthly expenses in retirement adjusted for <span class=\"lf-helpTab-tooltip-container\"><a class=\"lf-helpTab-tooltip\" href=\"#Inflation\">inflation</a></span>. Inflation has averaged between 2 and 3 percent over the past 15 or 20 years. Since your expenses in retirement change over time, it helps to think of retirement in stages."
    },
    {
      "textLabel": "Your early retirement years may include spending on travel, education, and recreation. You may also be caring for elderly parents. Your expenses are likely to be highest in this stage of retirement. You will want to begin thinking about <span class=\"lf-helpTab-tooltip-container\"><a class=\"lf-helpTab-tooltip\" href=\"#EstatePlanning\">estate planning</a></span> if you haven't already."
    },
    {
      "textLabel": "In your middle-retirement years, you are likely to have paid off your mortgage and other debts. Higher medical expenses may creep up on you. A budget-conscious lifestyle becomes more important."
    },
    {
      "textLabel": "Finally, in your late-retirement years, you may face larger medical bills. Sticking to a strict budget may be more likely. "
    }
